00:04:54.240 --> 00:04:58.300
he's the thing that chases Captain Hook.
It's funny and it still animated well

00:04:58.300 --> 00:05:03.199
but why didn't they just do the crocodile?
They just say he's gone but why? This

00:05:03.199 --> 00:05:06.800
octopus thing does the exact same thing
I don't get why they need to switch it

00:05:06.800 --> 00:05:10.810
out. But for the most part, what they do is
switch out or keep in is actually kind

00:05:10.810 --> 00:05:15.190
of welcomed and besides that's not the
focus the focus is on Jane interacting

00:05:15.190 --> 00:05:17.750
with the lost boys and trying to get
back her childhood

00:05:17.750 --> 00:05:23.860
which, yeah sounds a little familiar, right? I guess if
you do have to compare these two I would

00:05:23.860 --> 00:05:28.530
say Hook is the better movie but I don't
know for a sequel to Disney's Peter Pan

00:05:28.530 --> 00:05:32.600
this is kind of exactly what I would
expect. It has some really nice imagery

00:05:32.600 --> 00:05:36.260
like when Hook is taking Jane to
Neverland this ship is flying through

00:05:36.260 --> 00:05:40.930
London it looks amazing. There is a wonderful
scene at the end where young Peter Pan

00:05:40.930 --> 00:05:45.410
meets grown-up Wendy and it plays out
exactly how it should play out it's not

00:05:45.410 --> 00:05:49.850
too emotional but it's not too simple
either it's kind of how I think of the

00:05:49.850 --> 00:05:53.930
movie. If you're looking to find problems
with it you won't find any shortage you

00:05:53.930 --> 00:05:57.820
can definitely find things that don't
quite work or maybe you've seen in other

00:05:57.820 --> 00:06:02.470
movies and such but if you legitimately
want to see a sequel to Peter Pan and

00:06:02.470 --> 00:06:06.400
you want to know what happens, I think
this is a very delightful adventure. I

00:06:06.400 --> 00:06:10.150
was really surprised I was not expecting
to like this film I thought I was gonna

00:06:10.150 --> 00:06:14.250
hate it like all the other critics did but I
actually kind of enjoyed it. It's not

00:06:14.250 --> 00:06:19.540
grand or epic but it's simple and nice.
Did it need to be made? Probably not but

00:06:19.540 --> 00:06:23.790
since it does exist I think its fine.
I think kids can watch it and get a lot

00:06:23.790 --> 00:06:27.370
of laughs and adults can watch it and enjoy
some of the more emotional moments. It felt

00:06:27.370 --> 00:06:31.220
like the people making it enjoyed the
subject matter and weren't forced into

00:06:31.220 --> 00:06:35.729
doing it. They appreciated the magic and
the imagination and the humor and the

00:06:35.729 --> 00:06:40.160
artwork and they want to do something
very similar and in my opinion, they succeeded.

00:06:40.160 --> 00:06:44.450
I guess it's not a favorite for a lot of Disney
fans but for me I have no problem believing in

00:06:44.450 --> 00:06:45.670
fairies with this one.

